 According to Sgt. Thabitha Leshilo, Mhluzi police spokesperson, the police received a call about a baby in Extension 4. Upon their arrival, they discovered the baby wrapped in a blanket. The mother was nowhere to be found. Mpumacare Ambulance Services rushed the baby girl to hospital. They said she was very cold, but in a stable condition. Anyone with information about the baby’s mother can contact the Mhluzi police on 013 247 7396.  Verkeer kruie in digte rookwolke Road rage ends with murder Balju baklei om lewe en dood Dit is winter en die damvlakke moet daal? • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za 